CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 4, 1954, pg. 1 reads: "5th Prize - Mrs. Aliene Mellix, mother of little Paula Aliene Mellix, holds her baby daughter who was awarded the fifth prize of $25. The child is the daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Leroy Mellix, who live at 7220 Mingo Street, and have three other children."
TitMainTitle: John Ruffing Jr. presenting fifth prize to Paula Aliene Mellix, daughter of Aliene Mellix, in Centre Avenue YMCA during Carnation Milk baby contest
